alwaysApply: false
---

# TDD

- Write the failing test first, then the minimum code to pass, then refactor.
- Domain (`src/psalm/domain/`) and application layers must be unit-tested.
- Coverage gate is 80% (`pyproject.toml [tool.coverage.report] fail_under`).
- ML infrastructure adapters (`infrastructure/ml/`) are coverage-omitted and
  mypy-excluded because they run on GPU and wrap untyped libraries; test the
  logic around them with fakes/mocks at the application boundary instead.
- Prefer fast, deterministic unit tests. Mark slow/gpu/integration tests with
  the registered pytest markers so CI can run `-m "not gpu and not slow"`.
- A bug fix starts with a test that reproduces the bug.
